=== Factors Associated with Better Outcomes

Research suggests better outcomes are associated with:

    - *Shorter diagnostic delay*: Earlier diagnosis and appropriate management
    - *Younger age at onset*: Pre-adolescent onset may have slightly better prognosis
    - *Absence of comorbidities*: Children without additional chronic conditions fare better
    - *Adequate rest and accommodations*: Avoiding repeated severe crashes
    - *Family support*: Stable, supportive family environment

